Components:
 * AMI (Amazon Machine Image) - template, virtual machine that runs in the cloud which determines the OS eg 
 * Instance type eg t2.micro
 * Network settings
 * IAM Role
 * User data
 * Storage options
  / Elastic Block Store
  / Instance store
 * Tags - label you can assign to a resource
 * Security group - acts like a firewall control the traffic to the instance
 * Key pair - consist of a public and a private key
 
 
 // Amazon CloudWatch for  monitoring instances
     * Basic monitoring - every 5 mins
     * Detailed monitoring - every 1 min

// Reserved Instances (RIs) - best for long term workloads with predictable usage patterns
